SIMPLE: penta
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penta-
<hw>Pen"ta-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pref.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>penta-</grk>, a later combining form of <grk>pe`nte</grk> five. See
<er>Five</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A combining form denoting
<xex>five</xex>; <as>as, <ex>penta</ex>capsular;
<ex>penta</ex>gon.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Denoting the degree of
<xex>five</xex>, either as regards quality, property, or composition;
<as>as, <ex>penta</ex>sulphide, <sig>containing five sulfur atoms</sig>;
<ex>pent</ex>oxide, <sig>containing five oxygen atoms</sig>, etc.</as>
Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentabasic</ent>⟦br⟧
